Preheat the oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop the potato chunks on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat in the oil, then roast onto the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Quarter the @apple{1} and remove the core. Thinly slice, then chop the slices into thin matchsticks. Pick the @rosemary{1/2%sprig} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pop a #frying pan{} on medium high heat (no oil). Once hot, season the @duck breasts{2} all over and lay the duck in the pan skin side down, fry until the skin is golden, ~{5%minutes}. Lower the heat to medium if it's browning too quickly. Turn and brown the flesh side for ~{1%minute} then transfer to the baking tray with the potatoes, keep the #pan{}! IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Pour some of the duck fat over the top of the potatoes, then return the tray to the top shelf of the oven and cook until the duck is cooked and the potatoes are roasted, ~{10-12%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The duck is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw duck and its packaging. Once cooked, transfer your duck to a #cutting board{} and cover with #foil{}. Leave to rest for a few mins.

While your duck cooks, return the now-empty frying pan to a medium heat with a glug of @oil{}. Once hot, add the @spring greens{150%g}, @apple{1}(thinly sliced) and rosemary. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the greens have just wilted, then stir in the garlic and a small knob of @?butter{1%knob} (if you have some). Cook for ~{1%minute} then transfer the greens into a #bowl{}. Cover with foil to keep warm while you make the drizzle.

Pop the @redcurrant jelly{50%g} and @water{2%tbsp} into a #saucepan{} on medium high heat. Bring to the boil, stirring continuously to melt the jelly. Bubble until glossy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Once the duck has rested, slice thinly and stir any resting juices into the drizzle.

Share the potatoes and greens between your #plates{} and lay the duck on top. Spoon the drizzle over the top of the duck. Enjoy!

